<title>ITALY: Italy ceramics firm Ricchetti makes bourse debut.</title>
<headline>Italy ceramics firm Ricchetti makes bourse debut.</headline>
<dateline>MILAN 1996-09-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Italian ceramics firm Gruppo Ceramiche Ricchetti started trading on the Milan stock exchange on Monday at 2,270 lire a share.</p>
<p>At 1012 GMT, the stock was quoted at 2,150 lire in volume of 1.1 million shares.</p>
<p>The Modena-based company is a leading producer of glazed tiles and had a net profit of 4.8 billion lire in 1995 on sales of 274 billion.</p>
<p>An offering of 34 million shares was made two weeks ago. The group has said it aims to use proceeds from the listing to reduce net debt which totalled 89.5 billion lire at the end of May.</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom +392 66129589</p>
